{
  "texts": [
    "Two experiments are conducted: in-domain (using AIDA-CoNLL corpus) and cross-domain (using all the other datasets).",
    "Cao et al. [29] present NCEL, a neural model for collective entity linking.",
    "NCEL includes three main compounds: candidate generation, feature extraction and neural model.",
    "Firstly, the generation of the different candidates is based on Wikipedia page titles, and a dictionary derived from a large web corpus and Yet Another Great Ontology (YAGO).",
    "Secondly, Neural Collective Entity Linking (NCEL) uses both local contextual features (based on similarity) and global coherence information (based on a window size for defining neighbour adjacency)."
  ]
}